  <h2>The Honest Trade-Off</h2>
  <p>A cash offer will typically be below full retail market value. That's the trade-off for speed, certainty, and zero prep costs. But when you add up agent commissions (5–6%), repair costs, carrying costs during 60–90 days on market, and the risk of a deal falling through — a fair cash offer often puts more money in your pocket than you'd expect.</p>
  <p>We'll always be straight with you. If listing with a Realtor is genuinely the better path for your situation, we'll tell you that.</p>

